    "headline": "This Memory Chip ETF Is Off the Charts. The Chip Stock Boom Is Only Part of It.",
    "summary": "The market’s appetite for memory chip makers is feverish, but this subset of the semiconductor industry might be looking a bit too hot.  Memory companies have been the latest beneficiaries of the artificial-intelligence investing craze, a boom that has lifted the entire semiconductor sector.  The reason is its focus on memory chips and its heavy concentration on three companies in particular:  Micron Technology  and South Korea’s  SK Hynix  and  Samsung  Electronics.",
